frameDefinitions: A Submittor gives Documents to an Authority so that they can be processed as part of an application, evaluation or other official or bureaucratic process.
A Donor transfers a Theme from a Donor to a Recipient.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
An Entity exists at a particular Location, at a particular Time, as observed by an implicit observer.
An object Theme moves in the direction of a Goal.
frameExamples: I  was sure I had passed as soon as I <t>handed</t> <t>in</t> the test. DNI
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
Liquid water was <t>present</t> on the surface of Mars billions of years ago.
Some students <t>arrived</t> at the school on Sunday.
listRoleDefinitions: The person that begins in possession of the <fen>Documents</fen> and gives them over into the possession of the <fen>Authority</fen> for processing.
The individual or organization that ends up in possession of the <fen>Documents</fen> and processes them.
The artifacts containing content, typically in the form of text and images, that the Submittor gives to the <fen>Authority</fen>.
The time period during which the <fen>Submittor</fen> gives the <fen>Documents</fen> to the <fen>Authority</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Submittor</fen> gives the <fen>Documents</fen> to the <fen>Authority</fen>.
The person that begins in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen> and causes it to be in the possession of the <fen>Recipient</fen> .
The entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The object that changes ownership.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Donor</fen> gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Donor</fen> gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The Creator creates a created entity.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.
The <fen>Entity</fen> whose existence at the <fen>Location</fen> is confirmed.
The <fen>Location</fen> of the <fen>Entity</fen>. The <fen>Location</fen> is conceived as a ground for an event of inspection to determine the presense of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Entity</fen> is present at the <fen>Location</fen>.
<fen>Theme</fen> is the object that moves. It may be an entity that moves under its own power, but it need not be.
<fen>Goal</fen> is any expression that tells where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up, or would end up, as a result of the motion.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when arriving occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the arriving event occurs.
listRoleExamples: The Human Services financial worker cannot decide if you will get food support benefits until <fex>you</fex> turn in the form and needed verifications.
If an application is late, whether you submitted it late <fex>to us</fex> or it was held up at your Command, NMETC will not be able to fund registration fees.

Once you have submitted <fex>the form</fex>, a request to make an oral statement will be
generated based on the information you supplied.
